cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with predicting 3D room layouts from a single RGB panorama. The use of deep learning and neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The mention of a dataset and experimental results suggest that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of feature fusion and network architecture could suggest that it belongs to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
